    "body": "One more thing I would like to add, for me it looks like erigon (and other clients) actually collect logs into some buffer, which means if there are a lot of different filters the memory starts to leak very fast. However, it should be trivial to reimplement eth_getFilterLogs/eth_getFilterChangs using eth_getLogs. We just need to store filter somewhere + track last seen block for filter, and then just run eth_getLogs.\r\n\r\nIt should reduce memory footprint significantly with tradeoff of CPU, however from my experience I don't see a lot of use cases for eth_getFilterLogs where latency is critical. ",
